        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(proxy): apply enhanced NO_PROXY matching to global undici dispatcher",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `HTTPS_PROXY` is set in the environment, `ensureGlobalUndiciEnvProxyDispatcher()` installs a global undici `EnvHttpProxyAgent` that routes ALL HTTP requests through the proxy — including internal plugin requests that should bypass it via NO_PROXY.\n\nThe built-in undici `EnvHttpProxyAgent` NO_PROXY matcher does not support:\n- **Leading-dot subdomain patterns** like `.myqcloud.com`\n- **CIDR notation** like `100.64.0.0/10`\n- **Octet wildcards** like `100.64.*`\n\nOpenClaw already has an enhanced `matchesNoProxy()` function, but it was only used by provider HTTP helpers — NOT by the global dispatcher.\n\n### Fix (revised per ClawSweeper review)\n\n1. **NO_PROXY-aware dispatcher wrapper**: Wrap the global EnvHttpProxyAgent so each dispatch checks OpenClaw's enhanced `matchesNoProxy()` before routing through the proxy.\n\n2. **ALL_PROXY kept SSRF-safe**: Unlike the previous approach, `hasEnvHttpProxyConfigured()` (the SSRF-safe shared helper) stays HTTP(S)-only. The global dispatcher uses `hasEnvHttpProxyAgentConfigured()` directly, which correctly includes ALL_PROXY via `resolveEnvHttpProxyAgentOptions()`. This is safe because the global dispatcher already runs inside the EnvHttpProxyAgent.\n\n3. **All construction paths wrapped**: `createNoProxyAwareEnvDispatcher()` is now applied in all three places that build an EnvHttpProxyAgent: bootstrap (`ensureGlobalUndiciEnvProxyDispatcher`), timeout hardening (`applyGlobalDispatcherStreamTimeouts`), and proxy lifecycle reset (`forceResetGlobalDispatcher`).\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Test matrix\n\n| Test file | Tests | Result |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| `proxy-env.test.ts` | 55 | ✅ Passed |\n| `undici-global-dispatcher.test.ts` | 33 | ✅ Passed |\n| **Total** | **88** | **✅ All passed** |\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Global undici dispatcher respects enhanced NO_PROXY matching (subdomain/CIDR/wildcard). ALL_PROXY deployments use the correct proxy routing without widening SSRF guards. Proxy lifecycle resets preserve the enhanced bypass.\n\n- **Real environment tested**: Local source checkout, Node.js v24.13.1, Linux x64\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  ```\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n  Tests  88 passed (88)\n  proxy-env — 55 tests (ALL_PROXY still ignored by SSRF guard ✅)\n  undici-global-dispatcher — 33 tests (reset path wrapped ✅)\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: ALL_PROXY-only environments route through the proxy. SSRF-guarded fetch paths stay HTTP(S)-only. All EnvHttpProxyAgent construction paths carry the enhanced wrapper. NO_PROXY bypass with subdomain/CIDR/wildcard works.\n\n- **What was not tested**: End-to-end with a real proxy and qqbot COS upload (requires live credentials). The enhanced matching is covered by unit tests.\n\n### Checks\n- Format: ✅\n- Diff: +15 / -10 (25 lines, <=300)\n- Branch: clean from origin/main\n- Lockfile: unchanged\n- SSRF boundary: preserved (HTTP(S)-only)\n",
